CNCP v1 23430
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#12307: Broken types when using render functions with generic components & defineModel",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:21:50.104366+00:00",
  "text": "Broken types when using render functions with generic components & defineModel\n\n### Vue version\r\n\r\n3.5.12\r\n\r\n### Link to minimal reproduction\r\n\r\n[https://github.com/DrWarpMan/vue-generic-bug](https://github.com/DrWarpMan/vue-generic-bug/blob/bca98a3c436ca893fa92e8dc2b866fbcf5ffe7dd/src/App.vue#L7-L13)\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nThe bug is described in the comments of the code.\r\n\r\n**App.vue**\r\n```vue\r\n<script setup lang=\"ts\">\r\nimport { h, ref } from 'vue';\r\nimport Comp from './Comp.vue';\r\n\r\nconst foo = ref<string>('foo');\r\n\r\n// val should be of type 'string', not 'unknown'\r\nconst FunctionalComponent = () => h(Comp, {\r\n  /* unknown */ modelValue: foo.value, \r\n  ['onUpdate:modelValue']: (val /* unknown */) => foo.value = val,\r\n});\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n<template />\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Comp.vue**\r\n```vue\r\n<script setup lang=\"ts\" generic=\"T\">\r\ndefineModel<T>({required: true});\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n<template />\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\nRender functions should have proper type based on the provided value to the generic component.\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\nRender functions have 'unknown' type, regardless of the provided value to the generic component.\r\n\r\n### System Info\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Any additional comments?\r\n\r\n_Issue was moved  from [language-tools repo](https://github.com/vuejs/language-tools/issues/4972)._",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: types",
    "need documentation"
  ],
